Here's a sample `.gitignore` file tailored for a MERN (MongoDB, Express, React, Node.js) stack application. This file will help you avoid committing unnecessary files to your Git repository.

```plaintext
# Node modules and dependencies
node_modules/
*.log
yarn.lock
package-lock.json

# Build output and compiled files
dist/
build/
out/

# dotenv environment variables
.env
.env.local
.env.development.local
.env.test.local
.env.production.local

# Debug files
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# OS and IDE files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
.idea/
*.sublime-workspace
*.sublime-project

# Test files
coverage/
*.test.js
*.spec.js
*.snap

# Babel and ESLint
.cache/
.babelrc
.eslintcache
*.eslintcache

# MongoDB
*.lock
.dump

# Misc
*.log
*.pid
*.seed
*.sqlite3
*.tar.gz
*.zip
!src/assets/**/